				\begin{document}$$\Delta {\text{LnTEM}}$$\end{document}ΔLnTEM adversely affect food security (− 0.708 at 1% significance level). Conversely, and in line with the long-run estimations, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Delta {\text{LnRAIN}}$$\end{document}ΔLnRAIN significantly induced food security in the short-run (0.113 at 1% significance level). The study reported a similar effect in countries such as Cote d’Ivoire (0.188 at 10% significance level), Ghana (0.285 at 5% significance level), Mali (0.442 at 1% significance level), and the Gambia (0.226 at 1% significance level).

